my birthcontrol i would like to know if anybody outhere can relate to what im going through i am a young mother of and have decided to go on birth control to prevent anymore children and focus on my little ones for now i decided to take mirena and iud that is hormonal and it prevents pregnancy for up to years i talked to my doc before puting it in its been about weeks since and now im going crazy i have the worst possible mood changes out of nowhere and for nothing i start crying and i snap at my hubb i scream at my kids and then feel like stabbing myself for it i have also expirienced nausea i know that these side effects are normal but i cant live like this until the years are over and i can take my mirena out i need help to learn how to cope with my sideeffects cause its harming my whole family need good advice thanks for reading i had the same thing happen to me in i couldn't handle the side effects so i had my mirena removed and went with paraguard the great thing about it that it's hormone free i'm not sure how it works entirely but it's a copper t that has tiny little strings that kinda hang out in the birth canal i haven't experienced one mood swing or any of that other crap i went through with mirena and you can leave this in for up to ten years if you can afford to remove the mirena and go with the paraguard best of luck to you Oral contraceptive Birth control Prostate cancer Intrauterine device Kender Miscarriage Breastfeeding Pregnancy Charmed Emergency contraception Cancer Fertility awareness Obstetrics Clinical depression Hypoglycemia Sharon Tate EastEnders Postpartum depression Androgen insensitivity syndrome Transsexuality Kodocha Childbirth Shaggy dog story Craps The Shining (film) Bipolar disorder Menstrual cycle Condom Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Phoebe Halliwell Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Paroxetine Milton H. Erickson Growth hormone treatment Sexual revolution Phoebe Buffay's songs Pedophilia Endometriosis Traumatic brain injury Abortion Pitaten Stil